Then they wouldnt take me home because they wanted me to stay. -.- So I ate a bunch of goldfish with Audrey and Jolinda while watching some guy look for his shoe. Finally I got home.. got online...made an idiot out of myself then went to bed! lol.

Well my cousin and her boyfriend came and fixed my tire. Turns out my spare had a bubble in it.. So.. we had to drive to the nearest shop thing which is 12 miles away. So I ended up working 2-7. 

It really pisses me off when people try to take advantage of me just because Im young. Young does not equal stupid.

Some people came in and tried to use these tickets today. Most game rooms give out tickets straight from the machine. However.. since they had not been to our game room before they didnt know ours doesnt.

So, they come in with their tickets trying to use them...

Idiots-"Yeah we want to use our tickets"
Me- "Uh.. sorry you cant use those here"
Idiots-"Why not? We got these tickets here."
Me-"Im sorry you must be thinking of another game room, because you did not get those here."
Idiots-"Yeah we did, we came in January"
Me-"Well, where did you get them?"
Idiots-"From that machine right there." 
Me-"Really? We just got that machine a few days ago."
Idiots-"Oh wait.. it was that one over there."
Me-"Look Im sorry, you didnt get those here. We give out reciepts not tickets."
Idiots-"That one girl gave us these tickets"
blah blah blah this went on for like 10 minutes
and it wouldnt have been so bad if they were just mistaken and admitted they were wrong. I know they did it on purpose because I have seen them do similar things at other places.
Instead they just kept on and on and were really rude to me... which I dont even know why I care.. but.. I just feel like slapping someone. ~.~
I was suppose to work this morning. However, I had a blow out. ~.~ Oh well... waiting for someone to come change my tire now. I guess I should really know how... but... I dont so...yeah.
